news.title: China Evergrande to get $818 million for giving up land use rights for soccer stadium
news.para: In a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange late Thursday, Evergrande said "the group's liquidity issue has adversely affected the development of and construction on the land" in Guangzhou.

news.title: Nashik: Forest department comes up with 2 BHK houses for personnel
news.para: While four such houses have been constructed in Surgana taluka, the remaining five will come up at Trimbakeswar and Igatpuri talukas of the district.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to enter name in land records in non-town planning schemes
news.para: VMC deducts 20-40% land from plots in the non-TP areas to ensure that it has land for various amenities and development when the TP scheme comes up.

news.title: Implement PMAY-G, else will reconsider funding other projects: Centre to Chhattisgarh
news.para: In a letter to Chhattisgarh Chief Secretary Amitabh Jain, Rural Development Secretary Nagendra Nath Sinha has mentioned that the state government has not shown satisfactory progress despite several letters and meetings in this connection.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Objections to proposed hike in circle rate will be heard today
news.para: After a gap of six years, the administration has proposed a hike in circle rates to the tune of about 10% for the financial year 2022-23.

news.title: Design and Construct acquires The Better Co
news.para: With the acquisition, Design and Construct hopes to expand their pan India footprint and to augment their existing service portfolio. Headquartered in Bangalore, Design and Construct which has presence in Hyderabad, Pune and Mysore, has been in the business of construction since 2020.

news.title: HDFC raises Rs 8,700 crore to finance affordable housing segment
news.para: "This landmark financing further promotes HDFC's longstanding mission to be the leading provider of housing finance in India. Proceeds from the social loan would go towards financing affordable housing loans," HDFC said in a release.

news.title: ED files chargesheet against Amit Bhosale, Ara Developers in Pune plot case
news.para: The plot was meant for the construction of a residential building for bureaucrats. After allegedly manipulating the rules, Avinash Bhosale purchased it and constructed the headquarters of his company, Avinash Bhosale Infrastructure Pvt Ltd (ABIL), on it.

news.title: Kanpur development body to sell 1,100 plots through e-auction on Aug 15
news.para: All plots are neat and clean and without any dispute and will be auctioned after conducting on site archival and legal examination of each plot. This is the first time that KDA is going to sell plots in bulk said Arvind Singh vice chairman KDA.

news.title: RBI hikes interest rate by 50 bps to pre-pandemic level
news.para: The repurchase rate was raised by 50 basis points to lift the interest rate to the pre-pandemic level. The 5.40 per cent repo rate was last seen in August 2019.

news.title: Collector can't revise stamp duty already levied and paid, rules Bombay HC
news.para: ​The HC quashed and set aside a show cause notice issued in February to the builder for attachment of his properties over default in payment after repeated demand notices to pay an alleged outstanding of more than Rs 1 crore.

news.title: No Gurugram civic body nod, five residential buildings razed in Silokhera
news.para: A team of MCG officials --- RK Mongia, Sandeep Hooda, and Naveen Bedi --- carried out the drive at Vijay Vihar in Silokhera.

news.title: Mumbai: EOW arrests Srinath Developer's director in cheating case
news.para: Interestingly, Ved is the same builder who was booked last week by the Tilak Nagar police for allegedly breaking into his flat which was sealed by the MahaRera officials for default payments.

news.title: IRDAI eases norms of bank bonds, InvITs/REITs
news.para: AT1 bonds have no fixed maturities and are raised to shore up the capital base. These quasi-equity securities yield much higher returns than traditional bonds as the risk is also larger.

news.title: Supertech twin towers' demolition possible on Aug 21 if 'charging' begins by Sunday
news.para: ‘Charging’, the term for packing explosives into the two towers, was supposed to begin on August 2, but deferred because the blast design and other aspects of the demolition are being scrutinised and vetted by the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI).
